            },
            "answer_text": "I do not lhave HIV. I do highly endorse Gary's answer. While not every HIV infected person will have the same outcome as Gary, he is very very correct in his statements about the long term effect of the ARVs, and the much more rapid progressions of things like heart disease, heart attacks and other chronic complications.  I also completely agree with him about HIV stigma. We continue efforts today to end it, but there are multiple complications. Think of the uproar against gay marriage, and you must know HIV is still today incorrectly associated with homosexuality. So stigma continues. You dont hear about HIV on tv much, and even medical practitioners often fail to consider it when checking for other STIs. My opinions are from my experiences having been a nurse fir 24 years working in ER, ICU, Urgent Cares, and HIV . Working HIV I had to notify those newly infected and get them into care providing personalized patient navigation. Often I did the same for those who fallen out of care who had been positive for years. Many of those I helped became my close friends. I hope this helps. And Gary, keep the faith-love you . Matt. ",
